      "blocks": {
        "question_K6V3iw": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How is this handle safer than a regular door handle?",
            "answer": "<p>The handle is much safer than a regular door handle. It incorporates patented mechanisms within it that provides safety and security features not found in regular handles.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_cNwnnm": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does the handle help to prevent people from breaking in?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Common methods for break-ins are breaking of the external door plate revealing the Eurocylinder for snapping, or accessing the door handle through the letterbox. Features of the handle, such as the patented Thumb Turn mechanism and curved door plate profile can help prevent a break in.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_Q6YFpX": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I still open the door quickly in an emergency?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Given the Eurocylinder is operated by the patented Thumb Turn mechanism, there is no requirement to lock the handle with the key. In an emergency, there is no risk of needing to unlock using the key; instead, the Thumb Turn can be easily rotated and handle operated to open the door.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_WHxJ6K": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What makes it better than door chains or surface latches?",
            "answer": "<p>Door chains are fairly rudimentary and can still break with enough force – either with a link bending open, or the frame fixing ripping away. Surface latches can also be broken past with enough force. Plus they are fairly unsightly. Our handle encloses all features away within the handle, and crucially holds the door firmly in place. This greatly decreases the possibility of someone breaking past.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_aqinjw": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I install the handle myself?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Installation is a simple process and requires a cross or Phillips screwdriver. No additional tools are required.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
